            {
              "id": "s1_p1_context_prompt_1",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Read the text carefully then do the following activities."
            },
            {
              "id": "s1_p1_context_prompt_2",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Today, there are some 43 million pupils and students in public schools at the elementary and secondary levels, and another 6 million in private schools throughout America. In other words, 88 percent of American children attend public schools and 12 percent go to private schools. United Nations figures show that in the amount spent on education per capita, the U.S. is ninth place in the world (behind Qatar, Sweden, Norway, the Netherlands, Luxembourg, Denmark, Switzerland and Canada)."
            },
            {
              "id": "s1_p1_context_prompt_3",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "Most historians agree that a great deal of the economic, political, scientific and cultural progress America has made in its relatively short history, is due to its commitment to the ideal of equal opportunity. This is the ideal of educating as many Americans as possible to produce an educated people."
            },
            {
              "id": "s1_p1_context_prompt_4",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "American education has encouraged more Americans than ever before to study for advanced degrees and to become involved in specialized researches. The belief that the future of society depends on the quantity and quality of its educated citizens is widely held. It explains why a great many Americans are still willing to give more money to education, even during times of economic difficulty."
            },
            {
              "id": "s1_p1_context_prompt_5",
              "role": "PROMPT",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "value": "(From D.K. Stevenson, American Life and Institutions)"
            }
          ]
        },
